{center}
{subhead}Sequencer: BarsnPipes V1.20{def}
{left}
{pp}
4/4/03
{pp}
Alfred Faust published version 1.20 of one of the best sequencer for the Amiga
called BarsnPipes on 1st April 2003.
{pp}
New in version 1.20: Screenmode requester, GadTools interface, most of the
requesters are accessable with the keyboard, CAMD library, new 32 colour design,
localisation and much more. If you are interested in the changes please have a
look at the history which is available in the BnP_Addenum.guide file.
{pp}
Download: {link http://www.alfred-j-faust.de/download/BnP1_20U.lha}http://www.alfred-j-faust.de/download/BnP1_20U.lha (454KB){end}
{pp}
This archive only contains the changed files if you are going to update
previous version.
{pp}
The source code of BarsnPipes was officially released on 25th May 2001 by Todor
Fay. Since Alfred Faust has developed further this pofessional program it is
Freeware.
{pp}